<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e111799.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Phylogenetic tree constructed for the members of the genus Synalpheus using the Bayesian Inference approach based on a concatenation of four genes: 16 S, COI, PEPCK, and 18 S. Bayesian posterior probabilities are provided above each branch. Taxa are shown as Synalpheus species plus unique identifier (see supplementary table S 1). Eusocial species are indicated with an arrow (red, WA = West Atlantic; blue, IWP = Indo-West Pacific)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/959366" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e111799.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Synalpheus sponjy sp. nov., holotype (FLMNH-UF- 14409). A anterior region, dorsal view B same, lateral view, C pleon, D telson and uropods, E third maxilliped." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/959367" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e111799.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Synalpheus sponjy sp. nov., holotype (FLMNH-UF- 14409). A major cheliped, B same, chela, C lateral view same, D mesial view same, E fingers minor cheliped, F mesial view same, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/959368" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e111799.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Synalpheus sponjy sp. nov., holotype (FLMNH-UF- 14409). A second pereiopod, B third pereiopod, C lateral view same, mesial view, D fourth pereiopod, mesial view, E fifth pereiopod, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/959369" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

